{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1341,"text":"Like most journalists, I'm an idealist."},{"time":3857,"text":"I love unearthing good stories,\nespecially untold stories."},{"time":9126,"text":"I just didn't think that in 2011,"},{"time":11583,"text":"women would still be in that category."}]},{"cues":[{"time":14538,"text":"I'm the President of the Journalism\nand Women Symposium -- JAWS."},{"time":18539,"text":"That's Sharky."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19715,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":21230,"text":"I joined 10 years ago\nbecause I wanted female role models,"},{"time":24058,"text":"and I was frustrated by the lagging status\nof women in our profession"},{"time":28281,"text":"and what that meant\nfor our image in the media."},{"time":32086,"text":"We make up half\nthe population of the world,"},{"time":34213,"text":"but we're just 24 percent\nof the news subjects"},{"time":36824,"text":"quoted in news stories."},{"time":38752,"text":"And we're just 20 percent\nof the experts quoted in stories."},{"time":42461,"text":"And now, with today's technology,"},{"time":44557,"text":"it's possible to remove women\nfrom the picture completely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":48588,"text":"This is a picture of President\nBarack Obama and his advisors,"},{"time":52484,"text":"tracking the killing of Osama bin Laden."},{"time":54596,"text":"You can see Hillary Clinton on the right."},{"time":57261,"text":"Let's see how the photo ran"},{"time":58605,"text":"in an Orthodox Jewish\nnewspaper based in Brooklyn."},{"time":62327,"text":"Hillary's completely gone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64064,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":66936,"text":"The paper apologized,\nbut said it never runs photos of women;"},{"time":70009,"text":"they might be sexually provocative."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71965,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":74099,"text":"This is an extreme case, yes."},{"time":76171,"text":"But the fact is,"},{"time":77362,"text":"women are only 19 percent\nof the sources in stories on politics,"},{"time":81505,"text":"and only 20 percent\nin stories on the economy."},{"time":86210,"text":"The news continues to give us a picture"},{"time":88115,"text":"where men outnumber women"},{"time":89751,"text":"in nearly all occupational\ncategories, except two:"},{"time":92489,"text":"students and homemakers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95001,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":96282,"text":"So we all get a very\ndistorted picture of reality."},{"time":100414,"text":"The problem is, of course,\nthere aren't enough women in newsrooms."},{"time":103544,"text":"They report at just 37 percent of stories\nin print, TV and radio."},{"time":108006,"text":"Even in stories on gender-based violence,"},{"time":111110,"text":"men get an overwhelming majority\nof print space and airtime."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114737,"text":"Case in point:"},{"time":116999,"text":"This March, the New York Times\nran a story by James McKinley"},{"time":119927,"text":"about a gang rape of a young girl,"},{"time":121605,"text":"11 years old, in a small Texas town."},{"time":124515,"text":"McKinley writes that\nthe community is wondering,"},{"time":127594,"text":"\"How could their boys\nhave been drawn into this?\""},{"time":131136,"text":"\"Drawn into this\" --"},{"time":132564,"text":"like they were seduced\ninto committing an act of violence."},{"time":135668,"text":"And the first person he quotes says,"},{"time":137677,"text":"\"These boys will have to live\nwith this the rest of their lives.\""},{"time":140774,"text":"(Groans, laughter)"},{"time":143636,"text":"You don't hear much\nabout the 11-year-old victim,"},{"time":146644,"text":"except that she wore clothes\nthat were a little old for her"},{"time":150085,"text":"and she wore makeup."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152223,"text":"The Times was deluged with criticism."},{"time":155370,"text":"Initially, it defended itself,"},{"time":156973,"text":"and said, \"These aren't our views."},{"time":158718,"text":"This is what we found in our reporting.\""},{"time":160670,"text":"Now, here's a secret\nyou probably know already:"},{"time":163492,"text":"Your stories are constructed."},{"time":165114,"text":"As reporters, we research, we interview."},{"time":168159,"text":"We try to give a good picture of reality."},{"time":171091,"text":"We also have our own unconscious biases."},{"time":173860,"text":"But The Times makes it sound like anyone\nwould have reported this story"},{"time":177407,"text":"the same way."},{"time":179175,"text":"I disagree with that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181083,"text":"So three weeks later,"},{"time":182859,"text":"The Times revisits the story."},{"time":184410,"text":"This time, it adds another byline\nto it with McKinley's:"},{"time":188183,"text":"Erica Goode."},{"time":189683,"text":"What emerges is a truly sad, horrific tale"},{"time":192609,"text":"of a young girl and her family\ntrapped in poverty."},{"time":195592,"text":"She was raped numerous times by many men."},{"time":198703,"text":"She had been a bright, easygoing girl."},{"time":201117,"text":"She was maturing quickly, physically,"},{"time":203703,"text":"but her bed was still covered\nwith stuffed animals."},{"time":206719,"text":"It's a very different picture."},{"time":208640,"text":"Perhaps the addition of Ms. Goode\nis what made this story more complete."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212960,"text":"The Global Media Monitoring Project\nhas found that stories by female reporters"},{"time":217094,"text":"are more likely to challenge stereotypes\nthan those by male reporters."},{"time":220887,"text":"At KUNM here in Albuquerque,"},{"time":222284,"text":"Elaine Baumgartel\ndid some graduate research"},{"time":224443,"text":"on the coverage of violence against women."},{"time":226736,"text":"What she found was many of these\nstories tend to blame victims"},{"time":230133,"text":"and devalue their lives."},{"time":231676,"text":"They tend to sensationalize,\nand they lack context."},{"time":235423,"text":"So for her graduate work,"},{"time":236662,"text":"she did a three-part series\non the murder of 11 women,"},{"time":239583,"text":"found buried on Albuquerque's West Mesa."},{"time":242183,"text":"She tried to challenge those patterns\nand stereotypes in her work"},{"time":245571,"text":"and she tried to show\nthe challenges that journalists face"},{"time":248436,"text":"from external sources,\ntheir own internal biases"},{"time":251980,"text":"and cultural norms."},{"time":253652,"text":"And she worked with an editor\nat National Public Radio"},{"time":256399,"text":"to try to get a story aired nationally."},{"time":258956,"text":"She's not sure that would have happened\nif the editor had not been a female."}]},{"cues":[{"time":263472,"text":"Stories in the news"},{"time":264695,"text":"are more than twice as likely\nto present women as victims than men,"},{"time":268956,"text":"and women are more likely to be defined\nby their body parts."},{"time":273562,"text":"Wired magazine, November 2010."},{"time":276440,"text":"Yes, the issue was about\nbreast-tissue engineering."},{"time":280769,"text":"Now I know you're all distracted,\nso I'll take that off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283467,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":284492,"text":"Eyes up here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285670,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":288946,"text":"So --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":290121,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":294323,"text":"Here's the thing:"},{"time":295507,"text":"Wired almost never puts\nwomen on its cover."},{"time":298414,"text":"Oh, there have been some gimmicky ones --"},{"time":300415,"text":"Pam from \"The Office,\""},{"time":302041,"text":"manga girls,"},{"time":303974,"text":"a voluptuous model\ncovered in synthetic diamonds."},{"time":307863,"text":"Texas State University professor\nCindy Royal wondered in her blog"},{"time":311455,"text":"how are young women like her students\nsupposed to feel about their roles"},{"time":315470,"text":"in technology, reading Wired."},{"time":316962,"text":"Chris Anderson, the editor of Wired,\ndefended his choice"},{"time":320239,"text":"and said there aren't enough women,\nprominent women"},{"time":322652,"text":"in technology to sell a cover,\nto sell an issue."},{"time":326581,"text":"Part of that is true,"},{"time":327764,"text":"there aren't as many\nprominent women in technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330336,"text":"Here's my problem with that argument:"},{"time":332850,"text":"Media tells us every day what's important,"},{"time":335453,"text":"by the stories they choose\nand where they place them;"},{"time":337980,"text":"it's called agenda setting."},{"time":340433,"text":"How many people knew\nthe founders of Facebook and Google"},{"time":343192,"text":"before their faces\nwere on a magazine cover?"},{"time":345384,"text":"Putting them there\nmade them more recognizable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348265,"text":"Now, Fast Company Magazine\nembraces that idea."},{"time":351085,"text":"This is its cover from November 15, 2010."},{"time":354371,"text":"The issue is about the most prominent\nand influential women in technology."},{"time":358827,"text":"Editor Robert Safian\ntold the Poynter Institute,"},{"time":361390,"text":"\"Silicon Valley is very white\nand very male."},{"time":364261,"text":"But that's not what Fast Company thinks"},{"time":366579,"text":"the business world\nwill look like in the future,"},{"time":368967,"text":"so it tries to give a picture\nof where the globalized world is moving.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":373354,"text":"By the way, apparently,\nWired took all this to heart."},{"time":376459,"text":"This was its issue in April."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378032,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":379934,"text":"That's Limor Fried, the founder\nof Adafruit Industries,"},{"time":382775,"text":"in the Rosie the Riveter pose."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385704,"text":"It would help to have more women\nin positions of leadership in media."},{"time":389198,"text":"A recent global survey"},{"time":390459,"text":"found that 73 percent\nof the top media-management jobs"},{"time":393349,"text":"are still held by men."},{"time":395335,"text":"But this is also about something\nfar more complex:"},{"time":397992,"text":"our own unconscious\nbiases and blind spots."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401817,"text":"Shankar Vedantam is the author"},{"time":403465,"text":"of \"The Hidden Brain: How Our Unconscious\nMinds Elect Presidents,"},{"time":406537,"text":"Control Markets, Wage Wars,\nand Save Our Lives.\""},{"time":409718,"text":"He told the former ombudsman\nat National Public Radio,"},{"time":412869,"text":"who was doing a report\non how women fare in NPR coverage,"},{"time":416630,"text":"unconscious bias flows\nthroughout most of our lives."},{"time":419744,"text":"It's really difficult\nto disentangle those strands."},{"time":423311,"text":"But he did have one suggestion."},{"time":425301,"text":"He used to work for two editors"},{"time":428116,"text":"who said every story had to have\nat least one female source."},{"time":432099,"text":"He balked at first,"},{"time":433616,"text":"but said he eventually followed\nthe directive happily,"},{"time":436592,"text":"because his stories got better"},{"time":438057,"text":"and his job got easier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440014,"text":"Now, I don't know if one\nof the editors was a woman,"},{"time":442636,"text":"but that can make the biggest difference."},{"time":445037,"text":"The Dallas Morning News\nwon a Pulitzer Prize in 1994"},{"time":449027,"text":"for a series it did on women\naround the world,"},{"time":451654,"text":"but one of the reporters told me"},{"time":453385,"text":"she's convinced\nit never would have happened"},{"time":455758,"text":"if they had not had\na female assistant foreign editor,"},{"time":459193,"text":"and they would not have gotten\nsome of those stories"},{"time":461701,"text":"without female reporters\nand editors on the ground,"},{"time":464216,"text":"particularly one\non female genital mutilation --"},{"time":467142,"text":"men would just not be allowed\ninto those situations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470220,"text":"This is an important point to consider,"},{"time":472478,"text":"because much of our foreign policy\nnow revolves around countries"},{"time":475758,"text":"where the treatment of women is an issue,"},{"time":478203,"text":"such as Afghanistan."},{"time":481578,"text":"What we're told in terms of arguments\nagainst leaving this country"},{"time":485726,"text":"is that the fate of the women is primary."},{"time":489701,"text":"Now, I'm sure a male reporter in Kabul\ncan find women to interview."},{"time":493835,"text":"Not so sure about rural,\ntraditional areas,"},{"time":497631,"text":"where I'm guessing\nwomen can't talk to strange men."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500858,"text":"It's important to keep talking about this,\nin light of Lara Logan."},{"time":504881,"text":"She was the CBS News correspondent"},{"time":507057,"text":"who was brutally sexually assaulted\nin Egypt's Tahrir Square,"},{"time":509994,"text":"right after this photo was taken."},{"time":512133,"text":"Almost immediately, pundits weighed in,"},{"time":514926,"text":"blaming her and saying things like,"},{"time":518189,"text":"\"You know, maybe women shouldn't\nbe sent to cover those stories.\""},{"time":521613,"text":"I never heard anyone say this\nabout Anderson Cooper and his crew,"},{"time":524874,"text":"who were attacked covering the same story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528387,"text":"One way to get more women into leadership"},{"time":530462,"text":"is to have other women mentor them."},{"time":532640,"text":"One of my board members is an editor\nat a major global media company,"},{"time":536257,"text":"but she never thought\nabout this as a career path,"},{"time":538917,"text":"until she met female role models at JAWS."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542425,"text":"But this is not just a job\nfor super-journalists"},{"time":544949,"text":"or my organization."},{"time":546152,"text":"You all have a stake\nin a strong, vibrant media."},{"time":549743,"text":"Analyze your news."},{"time":551474,"text":"And speak up when there are gaps\nmissing in coverage,"},{"time":554055,"text":"like people at The New York Times did."},{"time":556030,"text":"Suggest female sources\nto reporters and editors."},{"time":559410,"text":"Remember -- a complete picture of reality\nmay depend upon it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":563480,"text":"And I'll leave you with a video clip"},{"time":565219,"text":"that I first saw in [1987]\nwhen I was a student in London."},{"time":569137,"text":"It's for The Guardian newspaper."},{"time":570733,"text":"It's actually long before I ever thought\nabout becoming a journalist,"},{"time":574106,"text":"but I was very interested\nin how we learn to perceive our world."},{"time":578823,"text":"Narrator: An event seen from one\npoint of view gives one impression."},{"time":588579,"text":"Seen from another point of view,"},{"time":590355,"text":"it gives quite a different impression."},{"time":594982,"text":"But it's only when you get\nthe whole picture,"},{"time":597384,"text":"you can fully understand what's going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":603809,"text":"[The Guardian]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":605825,"text":"Megan Kamerick: I think you'll all agree"},{"time":607771,"text":"that we'd be better off\nif we all had the whole picture."}]}]}